09/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Public Order Minister George Voulgarakis said Friday (7 May) that he expects the Olympic games in Athens to be the safest in history. 
His comment followed a meeting with top U.S. 
security officials, including CIA Director George Tenet, FBI head Robert Mueller, National Security Adviser Condoleezza Rice and Homeland Security Secretary Tom Ridge. 
(MPA, Hellas News - 07/05/04)
